1
00:01:37,750 --> 00:01:40,416
[MORI] Powerful energy
reading. Overhead!

2
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:19,166
[GANZ]
Splendid work, Commander.

3
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:21,291
When we report this
to Major General Goer

4
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:22,875
we can hold our heads high.

5
00:02:22,958 --> 00:02:24,125
[SHULTZ]
I don't think so.

6
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:26,291
If that shameless
opportunist hears this,

7
00:02:26,375 --> 00:02:30,458
he'll report to Lord Desler as
if he'd conceived this himself.

8
00:02:30,541 --> 00:02:32,416
This is our victory and
we're going to make sure

9
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,708
<i>we</i> claim the spoils.

10
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:45,291
♪

11
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,958
Ilun Phezeron.
We have an incoming call.

12
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:08,208
Commander Shultz wishes
to give you a direct report.

13
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,666
Who is Shultz?

14
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:12,000
I believe you placed him
in command of

15
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,375
the forward base on Plat

16
00:03:13,458 --> 00:03:17,416
in the galactic hinterlands'
Zol system, my lord.

17
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,000
[DESLER]
Ah yes. I left a brigade of

18
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:23,458
second-class Gamilans in charge
of Teron's conquest, didn't I.

19
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:30,333
[footsteps]

20
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:37,500
[SHULTZ] I am Walke Shultz,
Commander of the forces

21
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,708
besieging Teron, my lord.

22
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:41,708
You are contacting us
without the approval

23
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:44,208
of your commanding officer,
Major General Goer,

24
00:03:44,291 --> 00:03:45,375
a grave offense--!

25
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:47,291
Now, now, Hyss,
I would like to hear him.

26
00:03:47,375 --> 00:03:48,500
Yes, sir.

27
00:03:48,583 --> 00:03:50,875
Go on, Commander.
Please give your report.

28
00:03:50,958 --> 00:03:52,458
Oh, yes sir.

29
00:03:52,541 --> 00:03:56,083
This morning, at Tahm 1006
Gamilan Standard Time,

30
00:03:56,166 --> 00:03:57,541
after fierce engagement,

31
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:59,625
we destroyed the
Teron FTL-capable

32
00:03:59,708 --> 00:04:03,958
spaceship <i>Yamato</i> using our
RSC as an improvised weapon.

33
00:04:04,041 --> 00:04:06,500
And you called to tell
me this why, Commander?

34
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:09,875
Well, sir. I-I wanted
to let you know

35
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:12,083
immediately about our victory.

36
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:14,375
So, you requested
a direct audience with me

37
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:15,791
in order to say that?

38
00:04:15,875 --> 00:04:18,291
An outcome so obvious
it was implied?

39
00:04:18,375 --> 00:04:21,416
I simply wished to add some
small measure of further glory

40
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,875
for the Great Gamilas Empire's
founding celebration.

41
00:04:24,958 --> 00:04:27,875
I shall remember
your loyalty, Commander.

42
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:32,125
That's enough!
Now get back to work!

43
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:35,500
Garle Desler!
Hail to our leader!

44
00:04:37,458 --> 00:04:40,750
So, Celestra. Is it true
a Teron ship has actually

45
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:43,166
managed to break
the light speed barrier?

46
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:46,291
That's the first I've
heard of it, Ilun Phezeron.

47
00:04:46,375 --> 00:04:49,166
How about you,
Viceroy Hyss, did you know?

48
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:52,583
Uh, I did not. This is
news to me as well, sir.

49
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:54,291
I assumed as much.

50
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:55,750
[FEMALES giggle]

51
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:09,833
[GANZ] Commander, what did
Lord Desler have to say?

52
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:13,500
He told me he would
remember our loyalty, Ganz.

53
00:05:13,583 --> 00:05:15,375
[gasps]

54
00:05:15,458 --> 00:05:18,041
It's a shame about the Terons.

55
00:05:18,125 --> 00:05:20,125
If they had chosen
not to fight back,

56
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:22,333
they could have lived
under the Gamilan thumb,

57
00:05:22,416 --> 00:05:24,416
just as we have.

58
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:33,083
[YAMAMOTO humming]

59
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:35,041
Hey SID. Tell me
everything you can

60
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,583
about our search zone.

61
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:39,041
[FEMALE SID VOICE 6A]
Executing command.

62
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:41,541
I've linked geographic data
with observed heat sources

63
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:44,458
projected as possible
sites of Gamilan base.

64
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:59,500
[ENOMOTO] Balance control,
are those vents closed?

65
00:05:59,583 --> 00:06:00,958
We're working on it, sir!

66
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:02,458
[ENOMOTO]
Work faster!

67
00:06:02,541 --> 00:06:04,416
Who wants to drown
on a spaceship?

68
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,083
Not me, damn it!

69
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,291
Hey! Prime the Extractor Pumps!

70
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:09,583
[MALE COMBAT OFFICER 6A]
We're closing this section off!

71
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:11,500
Get out of here! Aah!

72
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,666
[ENGINE ROOM OFFICER 4A]
Okay, it's contained over here.

73
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,958
[WOUNDED OFFICERS moaning]

74
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:21,000
[DR. SADO]
This wound's nothing.

75
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:22,666
With a little spit
he'll be fine.

76
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,208
Hey, Makoto!

77
00:06:24,291 --> 00:06:27,416
She's helping patients
in another section, Doctor.

78
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:30,375
[HARADA]
Hey, you still with me?

79
00:06:30,458 --> 00:06:31,791
Just stay strong, okay?

80
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:34,416
We'll patch you up right now,
you'll be fine.

81
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,416
All right, this one is stable.

82
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,875
Good. Give me a hand.

83
00:06:37,958 --> 00:06:39,416
Yes, ma'am!

84
00:06:42,083 --> 00:06:44,291
[HARADA]
See? You're all right.

85
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:46,333
So, were they able
to figure out how

86
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:47,916
the enemy was attacking us?

87
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,583
From what I've heard
they still don't know yet.

88
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:52,125
[MALE ANNOUNCEMENT 4A]
Damage Control Team Three

89
00:06:52,208 --> 00:06:53,458
report to Deck Four.

90
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:55,958
[YABU] Finished the check.
No problems yet.

91
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:57,291
That's good to hear.

92
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:59,541
What do you think, sir?
What's the plan?

93
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:01,083
How long are we
gonna have to sit here

94
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:03,833
hiding on the ocean floor?

95
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,875
We haven't even made it
out of our own solar system.

96
00:07:06,958 --> 00:07:08,500
Do you really think
we'll be able to make it

97
00:07:08,583 --> 00:07:10,708
all the way to Iscandar?

98
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:15,875
I will never let another ship
go down on my watch.

99
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:18,666
Since the first moment
I set sail from the earth,

100
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,583
my life's been in
old man Okita's hands,

101
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,250
and he's kept me alive.

102
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,625
If there's a way through,
then he'll find it.

103
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:26,833
That's all I know.

104
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:28,500
[SHIMA]
You're positive, sir?

105
00:07:28,583 --> 00:07:31,666
[SANADA] Yes, a
satellite-assisted beam weapon.

106
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:34,458
The large amount of orbital
debris made me curious.

107
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:36,958
So intel did more
thorough scanning.

108
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,750
[NIIMI]
They're not debris at all.

109
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:42,625
They're enemy satellites.

110
00:07:42,708 --> 00:07:44,458
We believe they're using
this immense network

111
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:47,583
to precisely relay a beam
which is fired from the surface.

112
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:48,750
If that's true...

113
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,166
They could hit any
coordinate around Pluto

114
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:52,250
and from any angle.

115
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:53,916
But that means there's
no way to escape.

116
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,666
If we surface
they'll hit us again!

117
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:58,166
[OKITA] Can we approximate
how much time we'd have?

118
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,625
I'll try, sir.

119
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:01,708
I hope our little fireworks
and acrobatic performance

120
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:03,833
were enough to
convince them we sank.

121
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:06,250
They're going to figure out
the truth eventually.

122
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,708
But for now, we sit tight
and put our faith in Kodai

123
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:10,416
and the rest of the pilots.

124
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:13,041
And when the time is right,
the <i>Yamato</i> will strike back.

125
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:15,041
And strike back hard.

126
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:18,333
[SHINOHARA]
Hey, Nemoto.

127
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:20,291
That rookie pilot's
a real babe, huh?

128
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:22,375
She sure can rock a flight suit.

129
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,916
[FEMALE SID VOICE 6A]
EM restrictions in effect.

130
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,333
Communication not sent.

131
00:08:25,416 --> 00:08:27,208
I know that, Navi-sweet!

132
00:08:27,291 --> 00:08:29,916
[FEMALE SID VOICE 6A]
Sorry, command not recognized.

133
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,500
Loosen up,
we're just havin' fun.

134
00:08:38,291 --> 00:08:41,083
♪ Protect me at night and
protect me during the day ♪

135
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,666
[FEMALE SID VOICE 6A] Sorry,
command not recognized.

136
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:46,833
Search target
in three megameters.

137
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:50,041
[KATO] EM restrictions lifted.
Come on Sugiyama, follow me.

138
00:08:50,125 --> 00:08:52,416
[NOBUHIKO]
Roger! Ugh!

139
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,625
Sugiyama!

140
00:08:53,708 --> 00:08:55,250
[FEMALE SID VOICE 6A]
Bravo 3 destroyed.

141
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:02,500
[KATO]
I guess we chose a winner, huh?

142
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,750
What do you mean
Teron fighters? Impossible.

143
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,666
Just outside the
Unmanned Environmental

144
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:10,375
Modification Plant
number 137, sir.

145
00:09:10,458 --> 00:09:12,041
What are they doing out there?

146
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:15,083
Anti-Aircraft System
engaging them now, sir.

147
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:17,000
It appears there are
several others coming out

148
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:18,750
of hiding as well, Commander.

149
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:21,500
Most likely survivors
from the <i>Yamato</i> .

150
00:09:21,583 --> 00:09:23,875
Launch the interceptors
to finish them off.

151
00:09:23,958 --> 00:09:25,333
Sir!

152
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:31,000
♪

153
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:43,666
[YAMAMOTO]
Beautiful.

154
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,458
[KATO] This is Bravo 1.
EM restrictions lifted.

155
00:09:49,541 --> 00:09:51,208
I've found the Gamilan base.

156
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:52,791
[KODAI]
Yamamoto, let's go.

157
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:54,666
[YAMAMOTO]
Wait!

158
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,000
[KODAI]
Is there a problem?

159
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:57,500
[YAMAMOTO]
Two o'clock.

160
00:09:57,583 --> 00:09:59,000
Two o'clock?

161
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:05,958
[AIHARA]
Message from Bravo 1.

162
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:08,708
Lieutenant Kato under fire
at Target Five.

163
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:11,000
He found it.
That didn't take long.

164
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:12,500
[OTA]
Coordinates confirmed.

165
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:14,416
--Good.
--Something's there, sir.

166
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,583
But we aren't certain
it's the enemy base yet.

167
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:18,375
Like any battle it's a gamble.

168
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:21,583
But you can't win the pot
without placing a bet first.

169
00:10:21,666 --> 00:10:24,500
Hm. Weapons Officer,
load the missiles and prepare

170
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,208
to launch them on our command.

171
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:27,958
Loading missiles for launch.

172
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:29,333
Engine status?

173
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:30,500
[TOKUGAWA]
Engine online.

174
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:33,791
We can reach maximum speed
on request, sir.

175
00:10:33,875 --> 00:10:37,416
Bridge to Boatswain. Are the
Wave Motion Shields charged yet?

176
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,791
[ENOMOTO]
Close enough, Captain.

177
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:41,041
Inertial Control's
back on line, too.

178
00:10:41,125 --> 00:10:44,458
Should be a lot easier to fight
with our feet on the floor.

179
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:47,708
Attention, all crew.
This is your Captain.

180
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:50,416
We will now convert to
undersea operations mode,

181
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,916
and engage in a
missile-based counterattack.

182
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,916
All crew to number three
battle stations!

183
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,166
Fire the engine!

184
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,666
[SAOTOME, YABU, YOSHIDA]
Yes, sir!

185
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:01,083
Blow the main tank
and start raising the bow.

186
00:11:01,166 --> 00:11:03,416
New angle, 35 degrees.

187
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,208
Turn us over!

188
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:20,750
[KODAI] Those enemy fighters
came from within the auroras.

189
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,291
That means...

190
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:29,791
[FEMALE SID VOICE 6A]
Warning! Warning!

191
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,541
Sensors detecting
unidentified energy emission.

192
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:34,666
Effect on ship unknown.

193
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:38,125
[rapid beeping]

194
00:11:38,208 --> 00:11:39,916
[KODAI gasps]

195
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:40,916
[YAMAMOTO gasps]

196
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,416
[rapid beeping continues]

197
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,125
[KODAI grunting]

198
00:11:46,208 --> 00:11:47,583
[gasps]

199
00:11:51,791 --> 00:11:53,583
Incredible.

200
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:57,000
[YAMAMOTO]
Lieutenant Kodai!

201
00:11:57,083 --> 00:12:00,750
I think we found it. This is
definitely the enemy base.

202
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,458
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
Movement on radar.

203
00:12:05,541 --> 00:12:07,958
Enemy fighters
directly above base.

204
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:09,416
What's that?

205
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,708
How is the
concealment field offline?

206
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:13,625
It's functioning properly.

207
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:14,708
What do we do?

208
00:12:14,791 --> 00:12:16,458
There's no need to panic, Ganz.

209
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:19,416
A few support planes
are nothing to fear.

210
00:12:26,375 --> 00:12:28,041
[YAMAMOTO]
Come on.

211
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:53,166
Direct hits to generators.
Concealment field dissipating.

212
00:13:00,875 --> 00:13:02,333
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
Concealment field offline.

213
00:13:02,416 --> 00:13:03,583
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5B]
Something is surfacing

214
00:13:03,666 --> 00:13:04,958
near <i>Yamato</i> sink site.

215
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:06,458
On main screen!

216
00:13:19,583 --> 00:13:21,916
[GANZ]
What is that? A submarine?

217
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,750
Use your head, you idiot!
That's the <i>Yamato</i> !

218
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:26,208
[GANZ]
Uh?

219
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:29,291
[SHULTZ grunts] This is bad.
I already told Lord Desler

220
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:30,583
that ship was destroyed.

221
00:13:30,666 --> 00:13:33,541
Now what are we supposed to do?

222
00:13:33,625 --> 00:13:36,500
You won't win, <i>Yamato</i> .

223
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:39,500
Ready Reflecting
Satellite Cannon!

224
00:13:39,583 --> 00:13:40,666
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 6A]
Preparing Reflecting

225
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:41,916
Satellite Cannon.

226
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,375
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 6B]
Calculating trajectory.

227
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:44,958
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 6A]
Selecting satellites for relay.

228
00:13:45,041 --> 00:13:47,291
Number 6. Number 33.

229
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:49,250
In the end,
this will all be irrelevant.

230
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,333
We will simply sink them again.

231
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:53,458
My report was merely
a bit early.

232
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:56,875
Nothing more.
The outcome won't change.

233
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:01,500
[AIHARA]
Preparing for missile strike.

234
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:05,958
Bravo 1, immediately
withdraw from the target area.

235
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:13,416
[KATO]
Easier said than done.

236
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,791
Bravo 1, do you copy?

237
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:17,750
[KODAI] This is Alpha 1.
Requesting combat support

238
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,208
from the <i>Yamato</i> .

239
00:14:19,291 --> 00:14:22,625
Alpha 1 and 2 have discovered
camouflaged enemy base.

240
00:14:22,708 --> 00:14:25,333
We don't have the payload
to destroy it ourselves.

241
00:14:25,416 --> 00:14:27,541
So that's the real base, huh?

242
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:29,125
[OKITA]
Good work, Kodai.

243
00:14:29,208 --> 00:14:30,458
[KODAI]
Captain.

244
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:31,833
[OKITA]
You see anything down there

245
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:34,083
that resembles a beam weapon?

246
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:36,875
[KODAI]
Negative, sir, not from here.

247
00:14:36,958 --> 00:14:39,416
They may have hidden it below
the surface or in the sea

248
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,250
to make it harder
to locate, Captain.

249
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,583
[AIHARA]
Searching now.

250
00:14:42,666 --> 00:14:44,625
We can't engage
in a full on assault

251
00:14:44,708 --> 00:14:46,416
until we've got
that threat off our back.

252
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,625
Alpha team, you are to
stay in the proximity

253
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:50,000
of the enemy base and stand by

254
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,708
to locate the source
of the beam.

255
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:54,500
How are we supposed to do that?
This base is gigantic.

256
00:14:54,583 --> 00:14:56,208
[OKITA]
Just keep your eyes open.

257
00:14:56,291 --> 00:14:57,458
[KODAI]
I don't see it!

258
00:14:57,541 --> 00:14:59,916
Trust me. You will.

259
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:02,875
[KATO] Damn it! They've got me
pinned at the wrong target!

260
00:15:02,958 --> 00:15:04,833
[SHINOHARA]
Stop complaining.

261
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:13,958
That's right.
The cavalry's arrived.

262
00:15:14,041 --> 00:15:15,791
[KATO]
Shinohara! Nemoto!

263
00:15:15,875 --> 00:15:17,416
And don't forget us!

264
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,625
Let 'em have it!

265
00:15:18,708 --> 00:15:24,416
[FIGHTER SQUAD cheering]

266
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:27,083
[SHINOHARA] They fly like
a bunch of thugs.

267
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:28,250
Let's go!

268
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:29,708
[FIGHTER SQUAD]
Roger!

269
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,708
Deploying reflectors on
satellites Number 6 and 33.

270
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,166
[NIIMI]
Got 'em!

271
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:39,250
Signals to satellites
have been intercepted!

272
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,791
Analyzer, now!

273
00:15:40,875 --> 00:15:43,125
[ANALYZER]
Beginning signal analysis.

274
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:44,625
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
Now deploying on satellites

275
00:15:44,708 --> 00:15:47,125
Number 28 and 57.

276
00:15:49,541 --> 00:15:52,208
[ANALYZER]
Relay satellites identified.

277
00:15:52,291 --> 00:15:53,750
Locking on nearest target.

278
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:56,666
AA interceptor missiles
ready for launch.

279
00:16:00,375 --> 00:16:03,458
[OKITA]
AA interceptor missiles, fire!

280
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:10,583
You've been lucky so far.
But you won't survive this.

281
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:14,250
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5B]
Energy charging complete.

282
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,000
Reflecting Satellite Cannon.

283
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:17,625
Fire!

284
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,250
[OKITA]
Well done.

285
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:40,708
[YAMAMOTO] Alpha 2 to <i>Yamato</i> .
I've spotted beam weapon.

286
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:43,333
Location is a frozen bay.

287
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:44,541
Copy that. Transmit the

288
00:16:44,625 --> 00:16:46,000
--coordinates now.
--[YAMAMOTO] Roger.

289
00:16:46,083 --> 00:16:48,750
Prepare to fire main guns
at the enemy beam weapon.

290
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,375
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
Satellite 57 lost,

291
00:16:50,458 --> 00:16:51,958
shot down from the surface.

292
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:53,166
[SHULTZ]
Looks like the <i>Yamato</i>

293
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,208
finally figured out
what we're up to.

294
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:57,625
Prepare the cannon to
fire again, on the double!

295
00:16:57,708 --> 00:16:58,916
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
Charging cannon now.

296
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,458
Our beam can
outdistance their missiles.

297
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:01,875
This time we'll change angles

298
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:04,208
and fire from
outside their range.

299
00:17:05,875 --> 00:17:09,125
Level the <i>Yamato</i> .
Main guns topside!

300
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:11,125
Adjusting inertial control.

301
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:12,875
Reversing the space gyros.

302
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:14,541
And dropping starboard ballast.

303
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:16,500
Leveling ship, now!

304
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,416
Leveling complete.
Inspection teams report

305
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,833
all systems are go.

306
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:33,666
Teams have set Type-3
rounds with timed fuses.

307
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:35,833
Our target is
the enemy beam weapon.

308
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:38,416
Load main gun
with Type-3 rounds.

309
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:44,250
Ranging complete.

310
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:45,708
Fire!

311
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:51,166
Countdown to impact.
Ten. Nine. Eight.

312
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:53,458
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5B]
Charging complete!

313
00:17:53,541 --> 00:17:57,041
[NANBU]
Seven. Six. Five. Four.

314
00:17:57,125 --> 00:17:58,750
Ready to discharge beam!

315
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,208
Fire!

316
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:07,625
♪

317
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:18,125
Alpha 1 to the <i>Yamato</i> .

318
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:20,625
Enemy beam weapon
has been destroyed.

319
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:21,750
We did it!

320
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:23,208
We're not finished yet, crew.

321
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:26,041
Now we will advance
and destroy the enemy base.

322
00:18:26,125 --> 00:18:27,791
Raise the bow by 20 degrees.

323
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:29,791
Take us into the sky!

324
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:40,625
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
No signal from

325
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:43,208
Reflecting Satellite Cannon.

326
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:46,083
This can't be true.

327
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:51,958
[sirens blaring]

328
00:18:52,041 --> 00:18:54,416
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
Yamato rapidly approaching!

329
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,291
Quick, sir. It's not safe here!

330
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:57,541
You have to leave the base!

331
00:18:57,625 --> 00:18:59,041
You want me to retreat?

332
00:18:59,125 --> 00:19:00,250
As long as you survive,

333
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,791
you'll have a chance
to redeem us!

334
00:19:01,875 --> 00:19:03,958
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5C]
All crew to battle stations!

335
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,708
Targets are locked
and ranging complete.

336
00:19:09,791 --> 00:19:12,500
Air-to-surface missiles,
ready to launch!

337
00:19:12,583 --> 00:19:15,041
Open fire, full bore!

338
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:47,125
Four enemy vessels.
It looks like they're running.

339
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:53,083
Pursue those ships.
And convert the main guns

340
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:54,916
to shock cannons.

341
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:21,375
We will stay here and
cover your escape, Commander.

342
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:23,541
Please be safe.

343
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:27,125
Prepare for Geschtam
Navigation! Hurry!

344
00:20:28,916 --> 00:20:30,666
Enemy ship heading
straight for us!

345
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:32,458
Draw their fire!

346
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:40,708
[yells]

347
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:47,625
[PLUTO BASE OPERATOR 5A]
The Destoria is lost!

348
00:20:47,708 --> 00:20:49,750
Geschtam Jump, now!

349
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,750
[MORI]
Enemy appears to have warped.

350
00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:01,333
What matters is the Gamilan
base on Pluto is destroyed.

351
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:03,166
The days of those
demonic planet bombs

352
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:05,666
striking the Earth are done.

353
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:09,333
[KODAI] Alpha 1 to <i>Yamato</i> .
We're headed home.

354
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:20,666
[DESLER]
Plat has fallen?

355
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,541
Tell me, Hyss,
was I having some sort of

356
00:21:22,625 --> 00:21:24,666
perverse dream earlier today?

357
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,083
I could have sworn I was told

358
00:21:26,166 --> 00:21:28,250
the Teron ship
had been destroyed.

359
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:30,958
It was no dream, sir,
that's what he said.

360
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:33,125
So Shultz abandoned his base?

361
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:35,333
And retreated
in the midst of battle?

362
00:21:35,416 --> 00:21:36,750
Yes, sir, he did.

363
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:39,458
Remind him retreat
is not a Gamilan concept.

364
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:42,666
It's "Victory. And if not
victory, then death."

365
00:21:42,750 --> 00:21:44,125
Sir!

366
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:52,333
Terons, huh?

367
00:21:58,166 --> 00:22:00,750
[OTA] The <i>Yamato</i>
has left Pluto's orbit.

368
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,041
Well, we pulled it off, Kodai.

369
00:22:07,125 --> 00:22:09,083
Yeah. We did.

370
00:22:10,250 --> 00:22:12,958
[KODAI]
That was for you, brother.

371
00:22:16,458 --> 00:22:18,541
Get us back on the fastest
course to Iscandar,

372
00:22:18,625 --> 00:22:21,000
set engines to combat speed one.

373
00:22:21,083 --> 00:22:22,250
[SHIMA]
Course adjusted, Captain.

374
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:24,166
Combat speed one.

375
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:19,916
[OKITA] With different emotions
in each of their hearts,

376
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:23,416
the crew of the <i>Yamato</i>
leave the solar system behind,

377
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:26,916
entering a galaxy which
human eyes have never seen.

378
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,041
Say a prayer
for those who set sail,

379
00:24:29,125 --> 00:24:31,833
and a solemn goodbye
to those left behind.

380
00:24:31,916 --> 00:24:33,958
Let your feelings be heard.

381
00:24:34,041 --> 00:24:36,041
We leave you, Earth,
but not for long.

382
00:24:36,125 --> 00:24:38,375
We will return!

383
00:24:38,458 --> 00:24:41,250
Next time:
"Farewell to the Solar System."

384
00:24:41,333 --> 00:24:43,416
There are 355 days left

385
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:46,333
before the extinction
of the human race.

